Police in Kariega are searching for a 16-year-old boy, last seen on February 28. Liyema Hlake, according to his mother, Nomakhaya, left his home in Sinqolamti Street, Gunguluza, KwaNobuhle, to go to school and has not been seen since. His family reported him  missing on March 2 at the KwaNobuhle police station. Any person that can assist the police in finding him  should contact  Captain Jessica de Klerk of the Kariega Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit on 071-352-4630, or by calling Crime Stop at 08600-10111.  HeraldLIVE